  <refentry id="function.pdf-open-image-file">
   <refnamediv>
    <refname>pdf_open_image_file</refname>
    <refpurpose>Lit une image depuis un fichier</refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
   <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
     <methodsynopsis>
      <type>int</type><methodname>pdf_open_image_file</methodname>
      <methodparam><type>resource</type><parameter>pdfdoc</parameter></methodparam>
      <methodparam><type>string</type><parameter>imagetype</parameter></methodparam>
      <methodparam><type>string</type><parameter>filename</parameter></methodparam>
      <methodparam choice="opt"><type>string</type><parameter>stringparam</parameter></methodparam>
      <methodparam choice="opt"><type>string</type><parameter>intparam</parameter></methodparam>
     </methodsynopsis>
     <para>
      <function>pdf_open_image_file</function> ouvre une image depuis le fichier
      <parameter>filename</parameter>. Les formats support&eacute;s sont
      <literal>jpeg</literal>, <literal>tiff</literal>, <literal>gif</literal>,
      et <literal>png</literal>. <parameter>stringparam</parameter> vaut soit
      "", <literal>mask</literal>, <literal>masked</literal> ou <literal>page</literal>.
      <parameter>intparam</parameter> vaut soit 0, soit la ressource d'image
      appliqu&eacute;e au masque, soit la ressource de page.
    </para>
   </refsect1>
  </refentry>

